<body>
    <h1>Executive Summary</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>This section describes a summary of the changes that were made t=
o the previous version of the requirement document. The previous version of=
 this requirement document is =E2=80=98Ascension-IAM Requirements Document_=
Draft_v0.4.</p>
<p><strong>Summary of changes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><u>"Scope"</u> section was updated with in-scope JML event list, number =
of AD domains, OIM as downstream application and OIM feed file generation f=
rom SailPoint.</p></li>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9C<u>Out of Scope</u>=E2=80=9D section was updated with new items=
 1) UKG account management, 2) OIM integrated target application management=
 and 3) fix gaps in existing SailPoint Platform.</p></li>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9C<u>Assumptions</u>=E2=80=9D section was updated with the follow=
ing additional assumptions: 1) existing list of integrated applications/int=
egrated systems are working as expected and 2) existing SailPoint platform =
is functioning as expected.</p></li>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9C<u>Workforce Management UKG</u>=E2=80=9D section was updated wi=
th the following&nbsp; additional points: 1) SailPoint to support manual re=
quest provisioning/de-provisioning and 2) SOD validation will be supported =
by SailPoint.</p></li>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9C<u>ServiceNow</u>=E2=80=9D section was updated with the followi=
ng&nbsp; additional items 1) SailPoint IIQ shall be&nbsp; source of truth f=
or account and access operations performed in ServiceNow, 2) SailPoint to s=
upport manual request provisioning/de-provisioning and 3) SOD validation wi=
ll be supported by SailPoint.</p></li>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9C<u>Oracle EPM Cloud</u>=E2=80=9D section was updated with the f=
ollowing additional items: 1) EPM module connector details and 2) SOD valid=
ation will be supported by SailPoint.</p></li>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9C<u>OCI</u>=E2=80=9D section was updated with the following addi=
tional items 1) SOD validation will be supported by SailPoint.</p></li>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9C<u>OIM</u>=E2=80=9D section was newly added with details about =
OIM feed generation.</p></li>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9C<u>Identity and Access Management Use-Cases</u>=E2=80=9D sectio=
n and subsections were updated for error handling, trigger condition, accep=
tance criteria, pre-conditions, and basic flow.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Additional Use-cases were added to cover =E2=80=9C<u>Secondary Work Rela=
tionship Provisioning (Associate)</u>=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9C<u>Secondary Work =
Relationship - Suspension (Associate)=E2=80=9D,</u> =E2=80=9C<u>Secondary W=
ork Relationship -Termination (Associate)</u>=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9C<u>Seconda=
ry Work Relationship Provisioning (NEP)=E2=80=9D,</u> =E2=80=9C<u>Secondary=
 Work Relationship -Suspension (NEP)</u>=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9C<u>Secondary=
 Work Relationship -Termination (NEP)</u> =E2=80=9C use cases.</p></li>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9C<u>Termination (Associates)</u>, <u>Suspension (Associates)</u>=
=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9C<u>Termination (NEP)</u>=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9C<u>Suspe=
nsion (NEP)</u>=E2=80=9D sections were updated with disconnected applicatio=
ns account handling as follows: A ServiceNow ticket will be created for eac=
h disconnected application team where the user account will be disabled. Ex=
isting SailPoint configuration will be used to create the ServiceNow ticket=
s.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Scenarios for non-worker user type have been added<u>(</u>=E2=80=9C<u>No=
n-Worker User Onboarding</u>=E2=80=9C<u>,</u>=E2=80=9C<u>Non-Worker User Of=
fboarding</u>=E2=80=9C<u>)</u>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9C<u>Suspension (Associates)</u>=E2=80=9C<u>,</u>=E2=80=9C<u>Leav=
e Of Absence (LOA)(Associates)</u>=E2=80=9C<u>,</u>=E2=80=9C<u>Leave Of Abs=
ence (LOA) (NEP)</u>=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9C<u>Suspension (NEP)</u>=E2=80=9D=
 sections were updated to cover the recall functionality.</p></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
